              Dearly Beloved, Kingdom Hearts re:CODED version was composed by Yoko Shimomura for the game's Original Sound Track. I chose this track to play on my website distinctly because of the sense of peace and safety it gives me, personally. I'm hoping it will also have a similar effect on my guests. I think it is very beautiful music, and it suits the theme of the site quite nicely. Just to be safe, however, I must repeat that I claim no ownership over this piece and intend no copyright infringement in using it for this project.  
          </p>
          
          <h3 class="loud">Why does the banner say "juno the mango loves strawberries"?</h3>
          <p align="justify">
              First, the "Mango" part is simply a pseudonym of my real name; and second, I really do love strawberries. Basically, that signifies the theme of this website as well as my online alias here. In reality, however, since the "strawberry" part seems to be unrelated to this site at all--my project originally intended to be the RbE project: or Rueberry Entropy, which is a site dedicated to everything related to strawberries. It would have been designed after the microsite I own, Rueberry. You may find the link in the <%= link_to "blog", port_blogs_path %> section.          </p>
            
          <h3 class="loud">Can I add you on Facebook/Twitter/deviantArt/Cure/Gaia?</h3>
